{"TopicId":221767,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Escaping Kerbin Mission Has Incorrect Objectives [asked to leave Kerbin SOI rather than to enter Kerbol SOI]","CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T16:53:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T16:53:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003ESee previous submissions for list | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 9 3900 12 Core | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GeForce RTX 206 Super | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the text of the mission \u0022Escaping Kerbin\u0022, you are tasked with exiting Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and heading out to orbit Kerbol.\u00A0 However, the objectives state only to exit Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and make no mention of Kerbol at all.\u00A0 This is confusing as, by the time this secondary mission comes up, you have, at a minimum, already sent 2 craft to the Mun.\u00A0 You have already left Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and entered the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of the Mun at least twice by this point.\u00A0 The mission objectives should be updated to state you need to orbit Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022QmBMkNT.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/QmBMkNT.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-22T16:56:25Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2023 04:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 22\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chewedbacca","CreatedById":230220,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-23T01:18:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this mission may also have a bug - could be related to the mission text. I put a craft into Kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E (i.e, orbiting Kerbol) and it did not register as a success. Happening for anybody else?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superluminaut","CreatedById":58963,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T18:12:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut technically you\u0027ve been in kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003Esoi\u003C/abbr\u003E the entire time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhereAreTheBathrooms","CreatedById":167730,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T18:28:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350618\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221767\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703268736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258963\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superluminaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Superluminaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut technically you\u0027ve been in kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003Esoi\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E the entire time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think this is how a new player with a burgeoning but still rudimentary grasp of the concept of an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E will read the situation. I agree with \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E that the game presents the impression during the Mun missions and tutorials that entering the Mun\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E means leaving Kerbin\u0027s, and that the mission objective should therefore clarify that the vessel must enter Kerbol\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E exclusively.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T18:34:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221767\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703269693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167730\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhereAreTheBathrooms\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, WhereAreTheBathrooms said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u00